[size=14pt][b]Great question about the 0.5 QUG reward![/b][/size] Let me explain the economic design principles behind Q-NarwhalKnight's reward structure.

[hr]

[size=16pt][b]📊 Current Mining Reward: 0.5 QUG per Block[/b][/size]

The 0.5 QUG reward is intentionally designed based on [b]Austrian economics principles[/b], specifically:

[hr]

[size=14pt][b]1️⃣ Sound Money Principles (Hard Cap)[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b]Total Supply:[/b] Fixed at [color=#FF4500]21,000,000 QNK[/color] (same as Bitcoin)
[*][b]No Inflation:[/b] Once all coins are mined, no new QNK will ever be created
[*][b]Predictable Supply:[/b] Transparent emission schedule, no central authority can change it
[/list]

This follows the Austrian school's emphasis on [i]sound money[/i] that cannot be debased.

[hr]

[size=14pt][b]2️⃣ Time Preference & Halving Schedule[/b][/size]

Based on Austrian economics' concept of [b]time preference[/b] (the idea that people value present goods more than future goods):

[code]
Block Range              Reward      Annual Emission
────────────────────────────────────────────────────
0 - 4,199,999           0.5 QUG     ~2,100,000 QUG
4,200,000 - 8,399,999   0.25 QUG    ~1,050,000 QUG
8,400,000 - 12,599,999  0.125 QUG   ~525,000 QUG
... (halving continues until all 21M mined)
[/code]

[b]Why 0.5 QUG?[/b] This creates a gradual, predictable reduction in new supply (halving every ~4.2M blocks), rewarding early adopters who take on more risk while still providing long-term incentives.

[hr]

[size=14pt][b]3️⃣ Austrian Business Cycle Theory (ABCT) Resistance[/b][/size]

Unlike fiat currencies that create boom-bust cycles through artificial credit expansion, QUG's 0.5 reward:

[list]
[*]✅ [b]Cannot be manipulated[/b] by central banks or governments
[*]✅ [b]No artificial credit expansion[/b] - all QUG must be mined (proof-of-work)
[*]✅ [b]Prevents malinvestment[/b] - entrepreneurs can calculate with sound money
[*]✅ [b]Eliminates Cantillon effects[/b] - no insiders get newly printed money first
[/list]

[hr]

